---
import KilocodeLayout from "../../layouts/KilocodeLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/quickstart-shared.css";
---

<KilocodeLayout
  title="Kilo Code Quickstart — Up and Running in 10 Minutes"
  description="Install the Kilo Code VS Code extension, run your first task, and start using AI-assisted coding with MCP tool support."
  currentPage="quickstart"
>
  <div class="qs-wrapper">

    <header class="qs-hero">
      <span class="qs-hero__eyebrow">Kilo Code · Getting Started</span>
      <h1 class="qs-hero__title">
        Quick<span class="qs-hero__accent">Start</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="qs-hero__desc">VS Code extension for AI-assisted coding. Task history, MCP tool support, context-aware editing. Works inside your editor without leaving your flow.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="qs-journey">

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">01</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Prerequisites</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">VS Code 1.85+ and an API key</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Kilo Code works with Anthropic, OpenAI, or any compatible provider. Get a key and have it ready.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>code --version</code></div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">VS Code 1.85 or higher required.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">02</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Install</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Install from VS Code Marketplace</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Open the Extensions panel in VS Code and search for Kilo Code.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">Cmd+Shift+X</span> → search "Kilo Code" → Install</code></div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Or install from the terminal:</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>code --install-extension kilocode.kilo-code</code></div>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">03</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Configure</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Add your API key</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Open the Kilo Code settings via the Command Palette and enter your API key. It stays local — never sent anywhere except the AI provider.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">Cmd+Shift+P</span> → "Kilo Code: Open Settings" → enter API key</code></div>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step qs-step--active">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">04</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">First Run</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Start your first task</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Open a project in VS Code, then launch a Kilo Code task. It reads your workspace automatically.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">Cmd+Shift+P</span> → "Kilo Code: New Task"</code></div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Type your first task in the panel that appears. Try: "explain what this codebase does and list the main components."</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="qs-milestone">
      <span class="qs-milestone__eyebrow">First Real Task</span>
      <h2 class="qs-milestone__title">Selection = context — try Explain Selection</h2>
      <p class="qs-milestone__desc">Select any block of code before running a task and that selection becomes your context anchor. This is how Kilo Code becomes precise instead of vague.</p>
      <div class="qs-milestone__steps">
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">1</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Open a file with a complex function.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">2</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Select the function body.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">3</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Right-click → "Kilo Code: Explain Selection" — or use the Command Palette.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="qs-milestone__cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">Cmd+Shift+P</span> → "Kilo Code: Explain Selection"</code></div>
      <div class="qs-milestone__steps">
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">4</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Kilo Code explains exactly that selection with full context from surrounding files. From here, ask it to refactor, add tests, or fix issues — it stays focused on your selection.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="qs-next">
      <p class="qs-next__title">What next?</p>
      <div class="qs-next__grid">
        <a href="/kilocode/tips/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">⚡</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Tips & Tricks</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Task history, MCP tools, auto-approve, checkpoints.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/kilocode/cheatsheet/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">📋</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Cheatsheet</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">All commands and shortcuts at a glance.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/kilocode/changelog/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">🔔</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Changelog</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Every Kilo Code release, tracked.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/kilocode/configs/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">⚙️</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Configs</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Models, MCP tools, auto-approve patterns.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.querySelectorAll('.qs-cmd').forEach(function(block) {
      var btn = document.createElement('button');
      btn.className = 'qs-cmd__copy';
      btn.textContent = 'copy';
      btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
        var code = block.querySelector('code');
        if (!code) return;
        var text = code.textContent.replace(/^(Cmd\+Shift\+[A-Z]|Cmd\+Shift\+P|\$)\s*→?\s*/i, '').replace(/^\$\s*/, '').trim();
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(function() {
          btn.textContent = 'copied!';
          setTimeout(function() { btn.textContent = 'copy'; }, 1500);
        });
      });
      block.style.paddingRight = '5rem';
      block.appendChild(btn);
    });
  </script>
</KilocodeLayout>
